      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:57:85",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/57/1177",
      "text": [
        " «تَؤُمُّهُنَّ فِي اَلنَّافِلَةِ فَأَمَّا فِي اَلْمَكْتُوبَةِ فَلاَ وَ لاَ تَتَقَدَّمُهُنَّ وَ لَكِنْ تَقُومُ وَسَطَهُنَّ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1177 - Hisham ibn Salim asked Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) about whether a woman can lead other women in prayer.\nImam (as) said: \"She may lead them in the nafl (supererogatory) prayers, but not in the obligatory (fardh) prayers. Moreover, She should not stand in front of them; rather, She should stand in their midst.\""
        ]
      }
    },
